This project has been developed in accordance with the Strategy for the Development of Vocational Education 2014 - 2020 of the European Commission, which gives priority to quality of vocational training of young people in order they to be relevant to the requirements of the labour market. "Improving the Students’ Professional Competence and Skills in an Intercultural Background" is a project in which the beneficiary is Knyaz Simeon Tarnovski High School of Economics, Stara Zagora, Bulgaria ( complete legal name- Targovska Gimnaziya Knyaz Simeon Tarnovski)  . The final- users of the project are 20 students from the High School, including 10 students from the 11th grade studying Economic Informatics and 10 students from the 12th grade studying Business Administration; two teachers - mentors; the headmaster of the High School. During the last week /five working days/ the headmaster will be monitoring the professional placement of students out at ADC College, London. The project’s partner is ADC College, London, United Kingdom. Practical training will be held in March 2015 in ADC College, London, UK. The acquired knowledge and placement skills during the training will be validated by: Europass curriculum vitae (CV), Europass mobility and Certificate of conducted mobility on professional placement in real business background. The internship, held abroad, will be considered by the High School of Economics as professional placement on the specialty with the decision of the pedagogical coucil.
European markets and, in particular, the Bulgarian market in times of economic crisis require competitive workforce, showing professionalism. There is a mismatch between the requirements of the labour market and skills of job seekers.
The main goal that sets this project is upgrading and improving their knowledge and skills of students by providing a work placement in an intercultural environment.
The specific objectives are:
- To create conditions for the development of professional skills and knowledge of the students;
- To encourage young people to learn about European innovative systems and best practices in order to improve the quality of professional training;
- To share best practices among the partner organizations;
- Encouraging mobility between European countries.
To achieve the goals, the project will go through three stages covering the required set of activities:
-Preparatory stage- sequencing of the programme with the  partner organization; organizational activities /to become aware of the  activities offered by ADC College, history of the college, the selection of end-users in the project,  preliminary acquaintance with the history and culture of the UK, making a presentation of the High School , insurances, travel tickets /;
-Real stage- conducting a three-week work placement in ADC College, London, practical training on the specialty through professional expert sessions, professional support, independent project work, presentations, and evaluation of  the results of the developed students’ projects and monitoring on the individual development of each participant, preparation of weekly reports and filling out questionnaires;
-Final stage- popularizing, reporting and multiplication of the project’s results at local and national level, analyzing the activities as well as the results of the project. Activities will be promoted among students and teachers in the High School, the Regional Inspectorate of Education, Stara Zagora, local business representatives, who must increasingly adapt to EU requirements and needs highly- qualified personnel, National Audit Office, Chamber of Commerce, Regional Agency for Economic Development, software companies and other economic institutions that are closely related to the provision of jobs for the conduct of students’ work placement.
The project participants expect to achieve long-term results that correspond to the reforms in vocational education at a state and European level:
• increasing as well as  improving the practical competence, knowledge and skills of the students in order to use them in their future career;
• encouragement of  the mobility between European countries;
• providing opportunities for students to apply what they have already learned in school through professional placement in multicultural background;
• encouragement of  young people to learn about European innovative systems and best practices in order to improve the quality of professional training;
• enhancing personal qualities in an unfamiliar environment;
• Users will have enriched the knowledge of the history of the United Kingdom, as well as be able to put into practice their knowledge of language culture;
• promoting of Bulgarian culture, traditions and customs.
The developed project is tailored to the specific priorities and objectives set out in the Regional Development Strategy of Stara Zagora for the period 2005 – 2015 as well as the High School Strategy for Development.

The main goal of the presented project School theory and practice abroad without any limits is the connection between the theoretical studies of students within the school with their practical activities in companies and the added value will be the development of their IT skills and the language professional competence. The internship is a part of the educational process 
and it provides a link with the theoretical technical subjects. The main goal is also to join as many students as possible into the practical learning, directly to the leading time activity and process of production in the differently specialized companies which production relates with our school specialization. It will be realized with the use of the most modern machine 
equipment. In these companies, there will be placed as many students as possible.
On the project School theory and practice abroad without any limits will be participating three partnersas follows: 
1.Secondary technical school in Snina, SR, as home organization; 
2.BaK production s.r.o. Písek, CZ, as mediatory organization; and host organizations in Písek 
– HEYCO WERK ČR, Ltd.; UNITERM, Ltd.; ELO+, Ltd.; PETOKOV, Ltd. – in this stage of the project preparation, they have already signed the documents of their acceptance and the letters of acknowledgement;
3.ADC College in London, UK, as mediatory organization; and host organizations in London centered on the IT, economics and administrative – we will have their list attached; we have the long-time experience with them, and after the selection of our students and the fulfillment of all the selection criteria, we will specify them more closely. 
The main goal of this project is to delegate our students to the internship into the companies with the most modern technological equipment. These companies will create for them suitable work conditions according to the work program. Students can use their modern technical machines which are for them new because they cannot manipulate with them during the time 
of their professional practice in our school. They have also no possibility to manipulate with them in the surrounding companies in their home-town. At the same time, they can improve their technical terminology in the foreign-language area and they will also be in touch with the company culture. 
Project is going to be realized as follows: 
I.In BaK production Ltd. in Písek and host companies in the Czech Republic – in activity A1 in two turns:
1st turn: term: 21.09.- 05.10.2014: 18 students and 2 accompanying persons 
2nd turn: term: 05.10.-18.10.2014: 18 students and 2 accompanying persons 
Students – they will be divided into the host companies according to their field of study: 
machine engineering, technology and transport operations and electrotechnics.
II.In mediatory organization ADC College in London and host companies in the UK – in activity A2 in two turns:
1st turn: term: 21.09.- 04.10.2014: 15 students and 2 accompanying persons
2nd turn: term: 05.10.-18.10.2014: 15 students and 2 accompanying persons 
Students – they will be divided into the host companies according to their field of study: technical lyceum.
Specific goals of this field-trip are: 
- to gain practical skills and experience in the contentual orientation to the students‘ 
fields of study and information and communication technology (ICT);
- to integrate internship participants into the work cycle in the cooperant companies; 
- to compare the last technical processes and trends gained throughout the theoretical learning and apply them into the practice;
- to make students familiar with operations and leading of the company, with the technological equipment in the host companies and also in other customer companies by the use of the technical excursion into them;
- to improve students‘ technical and field language competences in English; 
- in the final workshop – to evaluate the contribution of the mobility internship – to add some specific technical and field matters into the thematical educational plans and to make a discussion proposals for the subject komissions;
- to implement gained knowledge into the School Education Program; 
- every participant will process a presentation upon the topic of the mobility: Mobility internship according to me – report and contribution and suprise;
- from mobility internships – to create a calendar for 2015.
Participants finish the internship with the: 
- Certificate about the taking part in the internship, presentation and evaluation of their 
gained skills – from host companies and mediatory organization;
- Secondary Technical School Director’s Decision about the ackonowledgment of the technical practice – from home organization;
- certificate Europass Mobilita.

The project ICL - " In other country we learn" is directed to students attending vocational schools and who are enrolled in the three years of the course to obtain the level IV of qualification, one of the schools of the municipality of Paredes with vocational education. Also we will concentrate students that belong to poorest families and that way that will probably never have the opportunity to participate in future mobility experience .

One of the key objectives of this project is that participants develop through training practices in the workplace , personal , social and professional skills to complement the practical skills acquired in vocational training context . Additionally , this mobility will provide participants with the development of soft skills , such as language skills , integration in a context different from the place of origin of a contact experience with a work context in the training area that are attending , thus trying to their integration into the national or European labor market .

The ICL was planned to involve 30 participants who will carry out training practices for a month, in the begining of 2015 according to the availability of the various sectors of activity companies ( adapting to the professionals attending courses ) .

The Agrupamento de Escolas de Vilela along with APPIS will promote the inscriptions on the mobilities , and APPIS will select 30 participants . This association will plan jointly among partners the training program according to the characteristics / interests and skills of each participant meeting the specific needs of your area . Before the beginning of the period of mobility linguistic and cultural preparation will be carried out .

The host partners will select companies adapted for the reception of participants , conduct the training program and supervise/monitorize participants during the mobility with Agrupamento de Escolas de Vilela .

The training practices will be held in associated companies and will be evaluated according to the customized training program and Europass certificate with the same companies and additionally through a letter of recommendation produced by these .

The Agrupamento de Escolas de Vilela along with abroad partners (english and spanish ones) will provide all necessary logistics project ( accommodation, subsistence , etc ... ) measures .

All partners directly or indirectly involved in the project will carry out actions for the dissemination of project results.

Participants will receive a preparatory intensive course that will give them the linguistic and cultural knowledge to incorporate in companies. The courses will take place before the mobility and will be monitored by APPIS , in which a certificate will be awarded to all participants . The intensive courses of Spanish and English languages and culture will be held on Christmas lective interruption for 30 hours.

At the end of the project, we hope that participants achieve the following results :

- Increase of practical skills (learning procedures , self-confidence, self-efficacy , autonomy , teamwork ... )

- Increasing the language skills;

- Increased knowledge / reality of the labor market;

- Knowledge of companies that may be their employers ;

- Knowledge of the concept of European dimension and European labor market.

We expect the follow results for participant organisations (partners and host companies) :

- Increased knowledge of the European labor market;

- Exchange of good practices in each participating country ;

- Knowledge of new realities formative context ( youth ) ;

- Creation of other contacts for future collaborative projects , national and European ;

- Contact with the business world ;

- Knowledge of job profiles;

- Adapting the education and training path to labor market needs ;

- Validation of the practical application of theoretical knowledge acquired .

The current economic reality creates an urgent need for preparing young people to take on difficult roles of participants of modern market economy. The mobility project, which is a part of the program called Erazmus+ creates an opportunity to organize three-week apprenticeships for ten economics college students in British companies from March 2nd to March 20th, 2015. 
The project’s partners are: 
- on Polish side: Zespół Szkół Nr 10 im. Stanisława Staszica (sending partner);
- on British side: ADC Technology Training Ltd. (hosting partner).
The partners will do everything they can to meet the project’s goals with the highest standards and quality.
The main goals of the project are:  
- to upgrade the quality and effectiveness of professional training and teaching ;
- to gain practical and professional skills on European level ;
- to use the newest  information and communication technologies in the training;  
- to improve professional English language ;
- to increase professional mobility of young economists and their teachers;
- to increase the chance of finding employment in the European Union. 
The programme of training consists of the following modules: practical improvement of foreign language, getting to know the company’s functioning in its indoor and outdoor surrounding, commercial documentation, human resources politics, accounting and marketing activity of the company in economic market conditions. London is a perfect place for economic professional training, it has a special place on Great Britain’s market map and is a core financial and trade centre for the country as well as the whole Europe.    
Participation in the project is a great chance for young people to get to know market conditions of the partnering countries, as well as developing young people’s independence and abilities to manage themselves in a new environment. The project’s participants will be given an ADC College certificate and Europass Mobility document in Polish and English which provides opportunities for finding employment not only in Poland but also in the whole European Union. Each participant will receive references from their employer which will make their CV more attractive. The students will build up their portfolios in English with a detailed description of their apprenticeship. In order to complete the apprenticeship the students have to gain a grade consistent with the European Credit System for Vocational Education & Training.

The need for project implementation
Following the analysis done at the level of bilingual classes with a view to engaging students in the labour market, the school board and the Department of English assess the attainment of objectives set in the "European dimension and equal opportunities", from the Institutional Development Plan in order to:
- increase students’ employability (as translators in English for Specific Purposes, a profession highly demanded in the labour market);
- connect the school to the community through cross-sector partnerships;
- develop students on a personal and professional level in the spirit of active citizenship.
Conclusions of the analysis:
- students possess average and advanced knowledge, in accordance with the curriculum established level;
- students’ skills in translating language for specific purposes is not in accordance with the European quality standard;
- the work placement of students in the authentic context of the native bilingual translator is necessary in order to attain quality standards;
- the needs of the community in the field of translation in English for business purposes are identified;
- the school sets up partnerships with county high-schools having classes specialised in economic studies which are in need of translations for different materials used in the running of on line mock companies.
Project objectives:
- to develop competences required in the transfer of business English terms from Romanian to English;
- to offer the context for students’ participation in a practical work experience within an authentic environment of the labour market;
- to enhance personal and professional competences for lifelong learning;
- to promote the spirit of multilingualism as a symbol of the aspiration of students participating in mobility;
- to offer assistance in the professional development of students in economic studies classes, thus stimulating their access to the European labour market;
- to establish European partnerships in the fields of professional training and development of students in our school in order to improve their employability.
Participants:
The mobility is organised in two distinct flows of 14 participating students each and 2 accompanying teachers.
The participating students are selected from the target group (bilingual students in the 10th-12th grades), according to a methodology and a selection procedure established by the project team.
The principle of positive discrimination will be applied in the selection process in order to offer supplementary points in the evaluation form to students with poor social / family backgrounds.
Accompanying teachers and monitors are selected taking into consideration objective and transparent criteria and the process is similar to the one regarding the selection of students.
Placement activities:
- induction related to safety and protection of workers, setting up tasks and duties:
- text analysis from the point of view of specific terms and related domain, establishing the text-related terminology, validation by a specialist;
- editing and correcting the first version of the translation;
- linguistic revision of the translation (by another translator);
- specialist revision and stylistic revision;
- correcting the final translation and editing the final version;
- presenting the activity results;
- handing out certificates of participation in the placement;
- meetings to monitor daily activities;
- cultural visits. 
Impact
On the target group:
- students use the guide "Common Mistakes in Business English translation" (edited by participants in mobility in order to ensure the project sustainability) in the translation of the optional classes of translation;
- students become familiar with the techniques and work practices used in the field of translation at the European level (as a result of disseminations carried out by participating students);
- they understand organisation and provisions in an authentic working environment, which fosters employability.
At community level
- students in economic studies classes from the high-schools in the county use the bilingual textbook as a support for the activities performed within the mock companies;
- the school establishes cross-sector partnerships with companies interested in translations for business purposes („Mircea Cancicov” Business and Exhibition Centre);
- the school increases its attractiveness within the community and becomes a provider of workforce.
At national level
- bilingual students from high-school all over the country use the guide "Common Mistakes in Business English translation";
- students from economic studies classes in high-schools all over the country use the textbook and videos created during the support sessions offered by participating students to economic studies in high-schools established in Bacau County.

„Together in the Future of Technology and Business” is a European project of the Vocational School for Industrial Technologies, Management and Tourism, Panagyurishte. The partner organization of this project is ADC College, based in the central part of London in the United Kingdom. Both schools have a long experience in the field of information technology and business administration. The project provides a real opportunity to significant increase of the number of students who can participate in work experience abroad thanks to  the European Union. The partner organization provides us highly motivated team that tries to reduce the tension associated with the European economy and to improve intercultural communication, namely to help our students to refer to the differences between professional skills in the work environment. The project is short and will be implemented within one year through online learning and participation of students in practical training in order to exchange best practices. The training will be held in two professional fields: Information Technology and Media and Business Administration. 
The main objectives of the project are:
• Enhancing language learning in various forms;
• Developing programs and strategies to motivate students in their development as professionals - each in his field - IT and Media and Business Administration;
• Sustainable development of the school as a center for the creation of well-trained personnel needed for ever - dynamic economy, not only in the municipality of Panagyurishte, but also at national and European level;
• Research and analysis of the interests of future students of the school in relation to their chosen fields and professions;
• Development and participation in other European projects to motivate students and to bring additional resources to the school;
• To enhance the work experience in reliable partner-companies; 
• Use the opportunities for innovation in the teacher’s work;  
• Teacher’s participation in professional qualifications for getting effectiveness in their work;
• Developing strategies for the place and development of the school as a desirable area for students and education professional center in Panagyurishte municipality;
In this work experience 15 students are going to be involved, who will be accompanied by two leaders in order to organize a successful organization of the planned activities. Learners are aged between 15 and 19 years and they are beginners in the field of New Technologies. Ten of them are enrolled in a training course and practice in Information technology and Media, and five students are interested in participating in practical training in Business Administration. Skills to speak fluent English need improvement so  that may be realized in a real and practical environment.
In the first week both specialities will be included in the general English language course preparation.
In the second and third week, students from the field „IT and Media” will be engaged in activities related to Economic Informatics and Computer Technology:
• use highly intelligent technologies and software
• work with modern softwares
• application in specific activities and areas
• detection and removing of technical problems
• peripherals, allowing deeper penetration in computer systems and technologies
For the period from the second week to the end of the training, participants in the field of Business Administration will be engaged in the following activities:
• modeling and predicting management
• budget management
• making decisions and taking risks
• business games in management 
• business communications and correspondence
The successful implementation of the project will use modern and contemporary educational methods and approaches that will facilitate the management of this and other projects. Flexible methodology that uses the basic rules for making softwares and getting feedback. Applying interactive methods will encourage fast and flexible response to changes. Methods for the study of information systems are empirical (observation, comparison, experimentation, questionnaires, interviews and testing) and empirical - theoretical (analysis and synthesis, modeling, etc.).
As a final result, participants will receive a certificate of participation - they will have  greater opportunities to realize themselves on the local and national labor market, thanks to the knowledge, skills and competencies that will raise their authority and that of the school.
VET learning project aims positive implementation to our partners at local, regional, national, European and international level, we can create subsequent relationship with new partners that will lead to improve the mobility and the potential long-term benefits. Creating new jobs in companies-partners and opportunities for development of Information technologies and business are our long-term goals.

Thirty schoolgirls and schoolboys of Warcislaw IV Vocational School in Szczecinek will be participants of the project:
-          15 students of the 2nd and the 3rd hairdresser classes, hospitality classes and catering business classes in 2015;
-          15 students of the 3rd class of hospitality , the 3rd class of catering business and the 3rd hairdresser class in 2016 ;
Essence of the project is students’ participation in vocational training in London in companies of their specialty. British partner of Warcislaw IV Vocational School is ADC Collage. Nowadays we cooperate with ADC Collage in the project of Leonardo da Vinci program. Duration of apprenticeship is three weeks. Vocational training plan will be created on the base of educational programs, school work program and in cooperation with foreign partners. Our school has an obligation to create the best learning circumstances for students and the work placement abroad is manifestation of it. Foreign experience of our students will be very important on the labor market. What is more it is significant because half of our students come from rural area where unemployment level is higher  than average.
The most important aims of the project:
-          Participation in vocational training in companies in London;
-          Increase of competitiveness of the participants on the labor market after finishing school;
-          Improvement of quality of vocational education in Warcislaw IV Vocational School.
Before the departure the participants will receive pedagogical and psychological support. Moreover they will be covered by language and multicultural preparation.  Transport, care of English-speaking patrons from the school, care of companies’ patrons, food ,accommodation and entertainment will be provided to the participants . Responsible for realization and managing of the project will be appointed persons both from the side of applicant and the side of partner. Activities will be realized according to schedule prepared in cooperation with the partner. The  participants, the partners and the school will evaluate the realization of the program from the beginning to its end with the use  of school diaries, reports and tests. Final written evaluation with conclusions for future will be prepared by the headmaster, the person managing of the project and representative of ADC Collage.
The most important expected results:
-          Increase of a level of lingual and professional competency;
-          Increase of a level of interpersonal, intrapersonal and cultural competency;
-          Better preparation of participants to enter the labor market;
-          Improving of experience of Warcislaw IV Vocational School and ADC Collage staffs’ in field of international cooperation;
-          Improving of awareness of value of science and openness towards experiences among local society and students through dissemination of the results of the project.
 
 
Potential long-term benefits:
-          Increase students’ professional mobility;
-          Businessmen will receive better qualified and experienced employees in services connected to tourism;
-          Promotion of use of EU-programs among the local society, schools, teachers and students;
-          Promotion of Polish culture and education abroad.

Project “New Opportunities in Multimedia and Art“ was designed by Michael – Secondary school and Tertiary professional school of Advertising and Art, which is the only school of its kind in Czech Republic. The aim of the placement is to provide our teachers with the opportunity of comparing vocational educational practices in various countries. Moreover, we expect them to find inspiration for the development of curricula on which we are hoping to base the new study programme Interior Design, and new accreditation of the educational programme Multimedia in advertising at post-secondary level. 
Other expected outcomes include the uptake of the ECVET system coupled with the implementation of best practices, maintenance of our existing partner network and its continued extension via different communication channels (e-Twinning, Skype, e-mail), an improvement of the participants’ skills as well as confrontation of theoretical knowledge with job market needs. 
Our teachers will have the opportunity of discovering new technologies, work patterns and educational practices (through visits to schools) and comparing working conditions and environments in each of the countries visited (in particular through excursions to TV, film and photographic studios or PR agencies). They will find out about the knowledge and skills required of art school graduates abroad, which will represent a priceless asset for the continuous improvement of our curricula in the future.
Work placements are meant for both, secondary students and post-secondary level students. They will take place either in vocational schools (each of them has its own workshops and studios as well as contractual partners providing practical training) or directly in professional organisations such as PR agencies, photographic and video studios or regional TV broadcasters, DTP studios. The project seeks to respond to students’ need to complement theoretical knowledge with practical training by gaining hands-on experience in real-life working environments as well as in school workshops and studios, which will increase their chances to succeed on the job market.
The main aims and needs of the applicant and its partners:
• discovering new technologies and educational methods, trying out practical training and making use of the know- how of each of the participating institutions to improve the quality of own vocational teaching process;
• gaining international experience in teaching AV and multimedia production and applying the outcomes within methodological frameworks in order to create new educational tools 
• increasing cooperation between schools and training organisations (CZ, FI, ES, TR, UK, PT, SK, LV);
• using innovative solutions when cooperating with others (working within an interactive learning environment to increase the attractiveness of vocational subjects and language learning and bring them up to date);
• enabling students to take part in work placements with partner organisations while placing emphasis on self-development and international practical experience;
• raising intercultural awareness as a part of everyday life (a set of selected topics will be dealt with by each of the partners and the resulting portfolio will be published online);
• developing and implementing the ECVET system (designing units of learning outcomes for each placement and study programme) and making use of Europass.
Project outcomes will be implemented within methodology frameworks in vocational education and curricula development, thus improving teaching practices as far as vocational subjects and English are concerned. New study programme, improved practical teaching methodology and interactive learning tools: all these respond to job market needs and are meant to turn our school into a “modern European educational institution”.
Forming an integral part of the continuous education at school, the project will have a positive impact on teachers and students in that they will become more motivated and eager to upgrade both their theoretical knowledge and language skills. Information on the project, its implementation and outcomes will be disseminated through workshops, teacher conferences, Open Door Days, artwork (in particular via online channels such as Vimeo, YouTube or partner schools’ websites).

Earning Work experience abroad is one of the most interesting, motivating and challenging experience a  teacher can have.
The aims of the project named “Teachers for an Open Vocational School” proposed by  The Economic High School of Tourism Iassy  are:
- supporting teachers in their vocational training, having as a purpose innovating and improving the quality of teaching, training and of the activity in the field of economics, tourism and food industry, by workplace-based direct observation during  mobilities at ADC College Organisation;
- improving the linguistic skills of the teachers involved, as a means of promoting an effective and efficient communication in the educational system, both in Romania and in Europe; 
- raising participants’ awareness and reaction to social, cultural and linguistic  diversity;
- a better understanding of the British culture and of the feeling of being a citizen of the European Union.
-  increasing attractiveness and international size of the organizations involved in the vocational education;
- ensuring better recognition of the competences acquired during the period of vocational training abroad.
Eight teachers will participate in the project activities, people with a vast experience in teaching, concerned with continuing education, and who will benefit from an exchange of best educational practices with the representatives of ADC College, throughout the mobility.
The stages of “Teachers for an Open Vocational School” project are as follows:
October 2015:
- project team meeting for establishing the activity plan for implementing the project;
- promoting the project in school, for making an information panel;
- online promoting activities suggested for the project, which can be found on www.gsetis.ro and on school Facebook page;
- posting teachers selection information  for the group of beneficiaries of the mobility.
November 2015:
- selecting teachers participating in the mobility.
December 2015:
- publishing the list of teachers participating in the mobility.
January – February 2016:
- making all the necessary efforts to ensure logistics for the mobility.
March 2016:
- making cultural preparations for familiarisation with the particularities related to British customs and traditions ;
- training beneficiaries for risk prevention and individual safety.
April 2016:
- engaging in “Sharing Good Practice” mobility, at ADC College in London, UK.
May – June 2016:
- completing the mobility self-evaluation report and the questionnaires revealing the feedback for the partner who delivered the activities in the mobility;
- integrating the results of the educational activities performed by students, and promoting innovative approaches and best practice exchange acquired throughout the mobility;
- evaluating and disseminating results acquired throughout the project;
July – September 2016:
- making the final dissemination report.
The expected outputs will materialize as follows:
- 8 teachers as participants in “Sharing Good Practice” mobility – workplace-based direct observation;
- a brochure in computerized form including information related to the project;
- articles in local publications and in the school magazine;
- 5 project meetings with the project team members and the direct beneficiaries of the project;
- 1 workshop with the students of the school;
- 3 school site updates containing information related to the three distinct stages of the project;
- 8 feedback forms filled in by the participants in the mobility and by the country manager, from ADC College.
The acquisitions accumulated by the teachers participating in this mobility, will allow their professional development, which will generate a progress in training their students, thus contributing to increasing the rate of their absorption on the labour market, and, implicitly, the standard of living for their families. Moreover, the community will be at an advantage, by having a well trained workforce, according to the European standards.
By implementing “Teachers for an Open Vocational School” project, the image of Economic High School of Tourism will become more prominent at an international level, attracting new international partnerships for future Erasmus+ projects.
The participants of the two partner institutions will develop closer professional contacts, by using online educational platforms, as well as social networks, being motivated to get involved into other similar international projects.

The project “Fashion International Internship” (acronym FIT) is addressed to the training needs of young students, which have directed their studies at the fashion industry and clothing manufacturing.

The aim of the project is to promote the integration between skills acquired in formal educational contexts, learning on the job, organizational behaviour and soft skills,  in order to improve the preparation of students and support their future entry into the labour market.

Implementing FIT project, will be provided five weeks placements abroad in the summer, to 70 students of 3rd and 4th year of high school.
They are students from Institute "A. Volta "(studying section" Fashion System") and Artistic High School" San Leucio (studying section "Fashion Design").
Through the internship abroad, beneficiaries may improve their key skills, technical and  linguistic skills, by living an experience that integrates skills and knowledge learned at school, with training in the workplace, in an international context. The internships will take place in enterprises in the following countries: United Kingdom; France Spain Czech Republic; Portugal.

The project can produce important results, both within the expected learning outcomes for the students involved, both for the impact that the project may have on the local level and for the organizations involved. 
Specifically, the expected results are:
- contribute to the education of young people through transnational mobility experience, in order to improve their key skills, abilities, technical and professional knowledge in line with needs of labour market;
- promote the mobility of young people to increase their soft skills, including linguistic and cultural enrichment, which can affect their growth and employability;
- improve the educational offer of schools, by acting positively on the capacities of the institutions involved to enrich the curricula for learners with European experiences and methodologies;
- encourage the participation of companies, ONG; business associations and local authorities  in order to create europeans networks of organizations involved in educational and vocational training ;
- promote the professionalization of youth in a strategic sector for the regional economy;
- improve transparency in the recognition of qualifications, adopting ECVET key documents (Memorandum of Understanding, Learning Agreement, Personal Transcript);

FIT project, realized in the framework of  Erasmus Plus Program - KA 1 VET, is applied by a consortium of public and private organizations: Association Informamentis Europa (coordinator of the consortium); Institute Of Higher Secondary Education “A. Volta”; Artistic High School “San Leucio”; Confindustria Caserta; Chamber of Commerce Caserta; Company “Quaredo Confezioni SRL; Company “Setificio San Leucio” S.R.L .; company “A.G.K. ITALY S.R.L.”.
The consortium was created to encourage active cooperation between public and private organizations, that can provide innovative learning opportunities, in order to involve effectively young people in VET experiences.

“E.A.S.Y LAB - Entrepreneurship And Self-emploYment by real experiences in LABour market” aims at promoting the mobility of 60 graduates from specific professional and economic sectors such as wine, food, tourism and hospitality. The participants will be selected according to their motivation, determination, linguistic skills and will have the opportunity to carry out a 4-month internship in the abovementioned fields. These internships will take place in the following countries: France, Spain and United Kingdom.
The project aims to reach the following specific objectives:
- increasing the general awareness towards the possible opportunities that the wine and food/tourism industry could offer for youth employment and entrepreneurship;
- providing young people with the right skills required by the wine and food industry and touristic hospitality through a real working experience abroad;
- encouraging their personal and professional development and independence;
- developing specific managing abilities through a concrete professional business experience, which is going to contribute to the acquisition of those such as problem solving and decision making skills that will eventually fulfil the gap between the school world and the labour market;
- increasing the youngsters’ sense of belonging to the European community through their integration in an international environment;
- contributing to the development of the ECVET system (European Credit system for Vocational Education and Training) for a better and equal acknowledge of the professional skills acquired abroad.
IMPACT:
- the participants will benefit from the project by improving their professional and linguistic skills as well as their knowledge regarding the hospitality/tourism/ food and wine industries so as to encourage their integration in the labour market;
- project’s Consortium will benefit in terms of a better “internationalization “of Basilicata and the spread of its typical food /wine culture and tourism at a European level so as to increase the exportation of their products;
- as regards the local impact, at the end of the mobility, it will be held a further internship phase - paid by local partners - in local companies in order to make sure that the young generations will have concrete and real job opportunities;
- from an European point of view, the project will strengthen the international cooperation and it will promote a better consciousness of the Italian wine and food industry, history and tradition.
The project represents a great opportunity to reflect on the important role of tourism (in all of its shapes and directions) for the community and its economic development, for better chances of employability and , last but not least, for the promotion of those local and unique features that have always been characterizing the Italian territory.

ME.M.O.R.Y. - Mediterranean Memories and mobilities for young learners – was born from the analysis carried out within the context of Puglia region , from the recognition that the Mediterranean diet received from UNESCO in 2010 as heritage of humanity and the potential that such recognition may represent for the promotion of the territories in which it was born.
At the base of this project there is the idea that a full appreciation of the southern Italian regions of Puglia cannot be possible without an adequate training of human resources, both as regarding more traditional professionals as well as those emerging professional profiles

Hence, the proposal of a mobility experience abroad. This opportunity will be open to 100 young graduates (who graduated within a year from their application) residing in Puglia and specialized in vocational and technical sectors such as: tourism, hotel hospitality, agro – food industry. They will carry out an internship in the following  countries: Spain, Belgium ; Malta; UK. The mobility will last 122 days and will take place in European companies operating in the abovementioned economic sectors.

The desire to promote such a project comes from the awareness that the local labor market has little space for  developing  and "engaging" one’s own professional potential and knowledge acquired during the school years. The project aims at encouraging the revival of the local economy and the labor market in Puglia in relation to the agri-food sector and cultural tourism, considered through a proper European perspective (dissemination and visibility of the Mediterranean Diet as a dietary pattern) and in a bottom-up development. The project will involve a local partnership of schools, public and private institutions, SMEs and associations operating in a territorial context, which is rich in traditions. These same traditions in return will get in contact with many other local communities outside the national borders, so as to
strengthen the European ideal against the relentless defense of national identities.

Main purposes:
-to promote and implement a transnational mobility project aimed at a target (graduates) aspiring to work in agribusiness, tourism and cultural sector;
- to Identify new emerging professional profiles in the agri-food sector related to the Mediterranean diet;
-to create the right conditions for a new economic model based on the philosophy and values of the Mediterranean spirit and in support of European planning. An economic model able to act as a driving force towards a sustainable development that can face the challenges imposed by globalization;  
-to improve the "product / territory" through the exaltation of biodiversity, cultural identity and in terms of typical products and the collaboration  between tourism sectors, environment and agri-food and wine industry;
-to combine environmental sustainability of EU and national policies with the growth of the local socio-economic system, induced by the technological innovation required for the development of new working methods;
-to promote European mobility for learning purposes, ensuring maximum visibility of the project results;
-to enrich the participants’ profiles, particularly for what concerns their language skills.

Expected results:

-possibility for trainees to come back with the best foreign experience and strengthened in their cultural-linguistic, technical and professional baggage;
-more chances of finding stable employment opportunities within the local labor market (it is estimated that 20% of participants will be employed after their experience), or at least easier access to qualified job opportunities abroad (20% of them will be employed in foreign companies as a result of their mobility and that 15% will come back abroad to look for a job);
-improvement of management practices of international mobility programs, which will be integrated into academic programs, such as the experience of a more completed training in classroom: it is estimated that 25% of the participants will enroll in several university courses;
-possibility for government agencies, schools and businesses to acquire new skills and quality experiences in the main areas of the project, innovating and raising these professional fields throughout the South of Italy, due to the testimony and experiences of the beneficiaries,;
-increasing of the employment levels for at least 20% of the participants, thanks to the creation of work placements once they will return back to Italy;
-the establishment of local sectorial business clusters, both abroad and in Italy, including other transnational types of clusters.

Context/background.
The previous project “back in business”, aimed at getting internationalization back on track. After some years of less attention to internationalization because of organizational changes, international activities are welcome again. The previous project put internationalization on the agenda again and the enthusiasm with students, staff, board and management is back again. About a year later, it’s time to make the next step in making internationalization a necessary part of the strategic vision and mission.

Aims of the project.
• Translate the enthusiasm of participating students and staff into longer term policy;
• Involve more students and staff by giving them the opportunity to build experience in foreign countries;
• Build an international network of ROC Leiden itself;
• Build a solid cooperation with City College in Plymouth.

Number and profile of the participants.
• 30 students (level 3 and 4) from various branches;
• 10 staff members, selected on motivation, enthusiasm and the ability to build an international network and to contribute to the formulation of policy.
• 
Description of the activities.
• Realizing internships and/or study abroad for 30 students in three selected countries in cooperation with our partners;
• Realizing activities abroad for 10 staff members in order to support the students and to contribute to policy making;
• Working out the cooperation with City College in Plymouth.

Methodology.
The methodology of this project coincides with the education and training concept of ROC Leiden. In short: practice learning. The theory of change is that a considerable and growing number of people creates experience and enthusiasm  in internationalization by working and/or studying abroad. This is the fundament of policy making. Students and staff will also share their experiences with the workfield.

Results.
• Students and staff are satisfied with the possibilities and organisation of international projects;
• The management decided on a long term budget for internationalization as integral part of the long term policy;
• At least 30 students and 10 staff participated in the project “next step”;
• ROC Leiden enlarged their own network with one or more new partners;
• After this project, ROC Leiden becomes a solid partner and will share this and the network with ROC ID College;
• The expertise on internationalization is adequate;
• Students who are, after the participation in the project, better trained, better motivated and experiencing better positions at the labour market;
• Staff who are, after the participation in the project, better qualified to teach with enthusiasm and creativity and promote “learn to learn”;
• ROC Leiden is by realizing this project, a better school. By communicating this inside the organization and also outside, the image is improving and ROC Leiden will be more attractive to potential students.

Impact.
By realising this project with a number of teams, other teams will be inspired to take part in internationalisation. In the long run ROC Leiden whishes , by realizing the project, to contribute to a better understanding of and more effort into European and other international projects. This will also lead to a better intercultural consciousness and an open mind for new international possibilities.

